instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin generates control commands for the vehicle’s Adaptive Cruise Control (ACC) subsystem. Command types include enabling/disabling ACC, setting a desired speed value, and issuing an emergency braking request. These commands are formatted by the Data Translation FE (serialised, type‑aligned and unit‑converted) and transmitted to the vehicle over the same Wi‑Fi UDP link used for sensor data. Upon receipt, the Actuation functional element on the physical side decodes the messages and forwards the desired speed or brake command to the vehicle’s motor and steering actuators. The system provides execution confirmation through feedback of the updated vehicle state (e.g., actual speed), which is again processed by the Data Translation FE and sent back to the DT for monitoring. No explicit authentication or conflict‑resolution mechanisms are described in the documents."
]

